\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. P. vulgare} L., {\i Sp. Pl. }1085 (1753). Rhizome-scales 3-6 mm, ovate, acuminate. New leaves produced in early summer; leaves lanceolate; pinnae obtuse or somewhat acute, the basal pair not projecting forward; secondary veins with 1-3(4) bifurcations. Sori orbicular; paraphyses absent; annulus with 10-15(-20) indurated cells, reddish-brown. 2n = 148.{\i  Most of Europe, but local in the east}. All except Bl Cr Sb Si.
