\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. C. macrocarpa} C. Presl,{\i  Tent. Pteridogr.} 135 (1836) ({\i Dicksonia culcita} L'Hér.). Rhizome with setiform, ferruginous scales. Leaves 30-100(-200) cm, as long as or rather longer than wide, in a lax tuft; lamina triangular, 4- or 5-pinnate, coriaceous, shining, about as long as the petiole; ultimate segments inciso-serrate. Indusium reniform. 2n = 132-136.{\i  Açores; W. Spain and N.W. Portugal, very local.} Az Hs *Lu.
