\pard\f0\fs28 Rhizome subterranean, far-creeping. Leaves distinct; petiole long; lamina up to 3-pinnate; pinnae and pinnules with nectaries at the base; ultimate segments numerous, ovate to linear. Sori contiguous, on the marginal vein, covered both by the revolute leaf-margins and by the indusia.
